The paper proposes a framework for image retrieval using a classification network based on Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) to obtain semantic features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a fusion strategy to reduce storage and time consumption, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's use of semantic information and distance algorithms suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
